    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The interdisciplinary study of the mutually adaptive interrelationship of individuals and their near environment; involves aspects of demographics, home economics, housing, design, social services, and family behavior. For the study of the broader spatial and organizational patterns of people across the landscape, use "human geography."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Estudio interdisciplinario de la relación recíproca adaptable de individuos y su medioambiente cercano; incluye aspectos demográficos, economía doméstica, vivienda, diseño, servicios sociales y comportamiento familiar. Para el estudio de modelos espaciales y organizacionales más genéricos de pueblos a través de un territorio, usar "geografía humana".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>De interdisciplinaire studie van de onderling aanpassende wisselwerking tussen individuen en hun nabije omgeving; omvat aspecten van demografie, huishoudkunde, huisvesting, ontwerp, sociale diensten en gezinsgedrag. Gebruik 'sociale geografie' voor de studie van bredere ruimtelijke en organisatorische patronen van mensen verspreid over het landschap.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052378/Winkler Prins Encyclopedie (1990)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一門跨學科研究，有關個體與鄰近環境間的相互調適關係；涉及以下層面：人口統計資料、家政學、住宅、設計、社會服務以及家庭行為。若為更大規模探討各地人口的空間與組織模式，則稱之為「人文地理學」。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>O estudo interdisciplinar da interrelação mutuamente adaptativa dos indivíduos e seu ambiente próximo; envolve aspectos demográficos, economia doméstica, habitação, design, serviços sociais e comportamento familiar. Para o estudo dos padrões espaciais e organizacionais mais amplos das pessoas em toda a paisagem, use a "geografia humana". </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
